The program is correctly written, but it doesn't ensure that all events are
are approved before assigning lastApproved's value to event's id. This mean
means if any unapproved (false) event occurs after an approved one, the las
last approved id will be overwritten by this unapproved event and won't be 
recorded as the last successful approval. 

Here is a corrected version of the program:

```Tundra
val events = [
   { id: "A", approved: true },
   { id: "B", approved: true },
   { id: "C", approved: false }
];

var lastApproved = "none";
for(event in events) {
  if (event.approved && event.id > lastApproved) {
    lastApproved = event.id;
  }
}

print(lastApproved);
```
This program will correctly assign the id of the most recent approved event
event to `lastApproved` and then print it out, in this case "B". It compare
compares each event's id to `lastApproved` only if that event is approved. 
If an event's id is lexicographically greater than `lastApproved` (i.e., co
comes after alphabetically), the program assigns it to `lastApproved`.
